#: artemis/reporting/modules/command_injection_detector/template_command_injection.jinja2:2
msgid ""
"We identified that the following URLs are vulnerable to OS command "
"injection:"
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/command_injection_detector/template_command_injection.jinja2:11
msgid ""
"This was detected using a time-based (blind) technique: an injected sleep"
" command caused a reproducible delay in the response, which shows the "
"server executed it even though the command output is not visible in the "
"response."
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/command_injection_detector/template_command_injection.jinja2:23
msgid ""
"OS command injection occurs when user input is passed to a system shell "
"without proper validation, allowing an attacker to execute arbitrary "
"operating system commands on the server. This can lead to full server "
"compromise, data theft, and lateral movement inside the network. To fix "
"this, avoid passing user input to shell commands; where that is "
"unavoidable, use parameterized APIs and strictly validate and whitelist "
"all input."
msgstr ""
